The paper discusses security and privacy risks in online social networks, which are primarily related to computer security (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI, cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the risks associated with children using online social networks, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential solutions to these risks, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
